\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 [While the party is still going strong, Evan tells Maggie that he needs to leave a little early, because his mom is flying in from Florida to celebrate Christmas with him and Liz.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 \line Here are a few things to note when crafting this scene. These ideas can be implemented as subtly or as overtly as makes sense for your writing style and the overall narrative:}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li720\fi-270\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 1.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 Uncomfortable Truth: In a traditional relationship dynamic, Evan would likely invite Maggie, his girlfriend, to spend Christmas with him and his mother. However, the constraints of their "Love, Annually" arrangement and his impending break-up plans make this impossible. Evan's discomfort stems from this unspoken reality.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 2.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 Maggie's Perspective: Maggie likely wonders why she's not invited to Evan's Christmas gathering, but dismisses her curiosity. She might rationalize it, thinking it's too early in their relationship to meet his family. This keeps her oblivious to the true source of tension. <!$Scr_Ps::0>}
